As I live on, I'll make monthly payments.

106
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:59,260
It's fine. You've already paid back for everything.

107
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:02,420
You not being sick is enough for me.

108
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:06,290
I'm so proud of you and thankful to you.

109
00:08:06,290 --> 00:08:09,680
Me too. I'm thankful, too.

110
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:15,920
To you, Aunt, Seon Kyeong, and..

111
00:08:28,970 --> 00:08:32,830
So you're saying that all those writers you mentioned signed the contract with you?

112
00:08:32,830 --> 00:08:35,990
No, that I made plans to have them sign the contract.

113
00:08:35,990 --> 00:08:38,400
I got an office, too.

114
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,200
I'm thinking about naming the company Top Ten Media. What do you think?

115
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,800
Is that with the aspiration of becoming the top ten among the publishers or something?

116
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:47,960
No, I'm expressing my will to sign with only the writers who'll make it to the top ten.

117
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,520
Who are you expressing it to?

118
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:55,120
You. I heard you're feeling pretty okay these days, so I'm formally proposing.

119
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,070
Join my company. I'll be good to you.

120
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,570
How will you be good to me?

121
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:01,190
I have a lot of money.

122
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:04,230
Showing off with no proof. I could do that, too.

123
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:09,760
Then you show off with salary and position.

124
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:13,430
Would you like to be my show off, Team Leader Tak?

125
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:18,030
Gosh!  You must be confident to have those writers sign, huh?

126
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:21,390
Well... I can't say I'm not confident.

127
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:25,730
Then, why isn't Lee Hyeon in that list of yours?

128
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:30,190
You know her ranking's been going up lately.

129
00:09:31,420 --> 00:09:33,560
- I do know. 
 - Then, why aren't you holding on to her?

130
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,820
It's not that I'm not holding on.

131
00:09:37,850 --> 00:09:39,290
I'm just letting her be for a bit.

132
00:09:39,290 --> 00:09:41,060
Why do you let her be?

133
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:44,160
Is she a cultural asset or a piece of art? She's a human.

134
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:48,360
Grab her whether as a woman or as a writer. Don't regret it later.

135
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:51,560
She'll need some time.

136
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:55,250
Seriously.

137
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:57,190
Time my butt.

138
00:09:57,190 --> 00:09:59,690
Do you think time will just be there forever?

139
00:09:59,690 --> 00:10:02,730
You sound like a spoiled child.

140
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:04,360
I know well.

141
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:08,660
It's not time that you need. Courage is what you need.

142
00:10:12,170 --> 00:10:16,320
Hey, you're kind of cool.

143
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:20,900
- I can't believe I get to give advice to Cha Joo Ik. 
 - Cha Joo Ik?

144
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:24,600
You're not boss yet. I'm off.

145
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:28,490
I will think thoroughly about the proposal that you made before I give you an answer.

146
00:10:28,490 --> 00:10:30,360
Hey, did I raise you like that?

147
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,560
Why think thoroughly? Just think roughly.

148
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:35,390
Yes, that's how you raised me.

149
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:39,860
You're the one who should think roughly and move quickly.

150
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:45,760
But some feelings get clearer as time passes, no?

151
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,230
For example?

152
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:51,260
Like longing.

153
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:55,860
- You're such a smooth speaker. 
 - That's how I made a living.

154
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:59,700
Gosh, I thought I was the one giving advice today.

155
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,760
You're such a tiresome supervisor.

156
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:06,360
Why do you always have to teach me something and I always learn something from you?

157
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:09,030
- What? 
 - I'm leaving.

158
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,830
Bye.

159
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:19,470
Kids these days...

160
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,380
 Recharge.

161
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,170
 Why can't you even cross the street?

162
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,580
Noona!

163
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:16,110
Are you crazy?

164
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:19,100
Why are you holding my hand?

165
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,800
Wait up!

166
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,320
You're all healed. Gosh, your strength.

167
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,070
So what? Do you mind?

168
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:30,080
No, I'm happy.

169
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:34,230
Look! I'm wearing the sneakers you bought me.

170
00:12:35,050 --> 00:12:36,010
What do you think?

171
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:38,630
Today's fashion color is blue and gray.

172
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:40,180
That's cute.

173
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:41,800
Wow, that was mean.

174
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,830
Why are you saying like you don't care?

175
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:45,620
These are really precious to me.

176
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:48,200
Treat them preciously.

177
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,800
Look!  Can't you just feel the refreshing vibe?

178
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,540
Yes, so refreshing. It must be summer for you. Aren't you cold?

179
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:57,530
Since we're talking about it, can I have your cardigan?

180
00:12:57,530 --> 00:12:59,700
What?

181
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,080
Never mind.

182
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:05,020
Your cardigan and my OOTD don't really go together.

183
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:06,470
See?

184
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:09,020
I'm really sensitive with colors.

185
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:12,740
If I became a personal colorist, I would've been great.

186
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:15,480
It's still not too late.

187
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,740
Should I register you at an academy?

188
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:19,970
It's fine. I was just joking.

189
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:23,480
I have a real dream now.

190
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,710
A real dream?

191
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:26,090
What is it?

192
00:13:26,090 --> 00:13:27,480
I'm not telling.

193
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,370
Not until it becomes true.

194
00:13:29,370 --> 00:13:30,880
Hey!

195
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:35,260
I think it'll be too small for you. Do you really want it?

196
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:36,870
- Don't take it off. 
 - Fine.

197
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,660
- Yes. 
 - What?

198
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,820
- Take it off. 
 - Forget it!

199
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,950
Feel my arm. It's so cold.

200
00:13:42,950 --> 00:13:44,970
So cold!

201
00:13:44,970 --> 00:13:47,190
This is why you catch colds!

202
00:13:47,190 --> 00:13:48,690
- I don't catch colds. 
 - Sure, whatever.

203
00:13:48,690 --> 00:13:50,970
I'm really healthy. That's how I make it through.

204
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:54,400
So embarrassing!

205
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:58,450
It really feels like a miracle to me.

206
00:13:58,450 --> 00:14:00,520
Every morning I wake up,

207
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:04,500
I have to think if it's a dream or real.

208
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,530
It's real, Aunt.

209
00:14:06,530 --> 00:14:08,820
Noona, you drank all the herbal tonic I brought you, right?

210
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:10,700
It's because of that.

211
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,190
- Is it? 
 - It's not.

212
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:14,610
It's not?

213
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:17,760
Then... is it because of Aunt's home-cooked meals?

214
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,050
Is it?

215
00:14:19,050 --> 00:14:21,360
That does sound pretty convincing.

216
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,830
Then, what is it?

217
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:25,720
What can it be?

218
00:14:26,530 --> 00:14:28,060
Love.

219
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:30,000
Love?

220
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:34,290
You're right. It's all thanks to

221
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,390
my burning love towards you.

222
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:39,480
After experiencing this,

223
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,430
I learned so much.

224
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:44,430
So I'm moving back to Korea.

225
00:14:44,430 --> 00:14:45,730
- What? 
 - So suddenly?

226
00:14:45,730 --> 00:14:48,490
It's not sudden. I've been planning this.

227
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:50,950
Kevin is wrapping everything up.

228
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:54,380
I just can't go back

229
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:57,610
leaving you guys behind.

230
00:14:57,610 --> 00:14:59,890
Is Uncle okay with that?

231
00:14:59,890 --> 00:15:02,230
Kevin is really for it.

232
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:05,250
Kevin thinks family is the most important.

233
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:08,320
He's really excited to live with you guys.

234
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,670
Awesome.

235
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:12,240
Then do I get to eat your food every day, now?

236
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,910
Yes.

237
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:17,960
Make me work. That's why I live.

238
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:21,360
I also have something to tell you.

239
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,500
I'm going to work.

240
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:28,100
- What? Already? 
 - Huh?

241
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,670
You can't.

242
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:32,590
Right, Noona. Why so soon?

243
00:15:32,590 --> 00:15:34,410
I want to work.

244
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:36,210
The doctor said it was okay.

245
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:39,130
Did anyone tell you to earn money?

246
00:15:39,130 --> 00:15:41,860
Just rest a little more. It's okay if you do.

247
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:44,310
Yes, Noona.

248
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:45,690
Or should I give you some money?

249
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:48,160
I was going to give you anyway, so play a little more with that.

250
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,660
I'm sick of playing.

251
00:15:53,790 --> 00:15:56,580
Not.

252
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,870
Actually, I'm not sick of it at all.

253
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:00,500
It's just...

254
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,310
I want to play while working.

255
00:16:02,310 --> 00:16:05,250
I guess I'm not the jobless type.

256
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:06,930
No way.

257
00:16:06,930 --> 00:16:08,350
Your character is your life.

258
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:12,010
- Stillâ€” 
 - I'm really okay.

259
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:16,250
I can't live like a sick person forever. I'm so healthy.

260
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,080
I eat well.

261
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,460
That's true.

262
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:21,260
She twisted my wrist earlier,

263
00:16:21,260 --> 00:16:23,140
and she's just as strong as Hercules.

264
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:26,180
Why did you do something to have her twist your wrist?

265
00:16:26,180 --> 00:16:28,370
Giving her a hard time!

266
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:30,910
Aunt, seriously?

267
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:33,760
When she twists my wrist, I'm the one suffering. Not her!

268
